						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the floor of the kitchen in the Lakshmīnarasiṁhasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Kṛishṇarāya, 1529 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 145[1], Virōdhin, Vaiśākha śu. 15, Friday, lunar eclipse,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1529 A.D., April 23.</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift of land to god Narasiṁha of Kadiri by Veṅkaṭa-nāyuḍu. the son-in-law of Dēvani Kōnapa-rāyuḍu for worship and offerings to the god for the merit of the latter.</p>						

						</summary>
